{
  "title": "ISic003147. Byzantine Christian invocation",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/P5CBGI8K\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/P5CBGI8K</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"δωxά\n                    ζουδοξάζου\">δωxά-<br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>ζ<span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ο͡υ</span></span>  <span data-text=\"πάντεπάντη\">π<span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ά͡ν</span>τε</span>  <span data-text=\"ἀὲν\">ἀὲν</span>  <span data-text=\"ὦ\">ὦ</span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>  <span data-text=\"θεόsθεός\">θεόs</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\">l.1 reg., orig. ΔΩXΑ ΖΟΥδωxά ζου | l.2 reg., orig. ΠΑΝΤΕπάντε | l.3 reg., orig. ΘΕΟSθεόs</p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/P5CBGI8K\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/P5CBGI8K</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"δωxά\n                    ζουδοξάζου\">ΔΩXΑ<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>Ζ<span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Ο͡Υ</span></span><span data-text=\"πάντεπάντη\">Π<span class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Α͡Ν</span>ΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"ἀὲν\">ΑΕΝ</span><span data-text=\"ὦ\">Ω</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"θεόsθεός\">ΘΕΟS</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\">l.1 reg., orig. ΔΩXΑ ΖΟΥδωxά ζου | l.2 reg., orig. ΠΑΝΤΕπάντε | l.3 reg., orig. ΘΕΟSθεόs</p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003147_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; Bonacasa 1955: fig.2\" src=\"ISic003147_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003147.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; Bonacasa 1955: fig.2\" src=\"ISic003147-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text from Bonacasa 1955</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>You are held in honour everywhere and always, o lord.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Note the uneven choice of letter forms, and the switch to Latin characters on two occasions. Earlier editors assumed the text was neo-punic or proto-Sicilian.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 18.0409.a <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Bonacasa 1955 269-271 figs.1-2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002132\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002132</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>cursive and majiscule alpha, uncial omega, lunate epsilon, use of later Greek ου ligature, use of X for ξ and S for Σ</p> Line 1-3  60-80  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
